  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "2BjKrLLXv2lVF0wPWGsuQG7B/c0=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:48.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "All sync data is encrypted with AES-256-GCM in the browser before it leaves the machine; the Bee node never sees plaintext. The encryption key is derived deterministically from the user's wallet so the same user on any device recovers the same key without a server.\n\nDerivation steps:\n\n1. User connects MetaMask.\n2. User signs a domain-specific message via `personal_sign`.\n3. `keccak256(signature)` produces a 32-byte secp256k1 private key.\n4. `SHA-256(private_key)` produces the 32-byte AES-256 encryption key.\n\nThe ciphertext format is `[SWE prefix (3 bytes)] [IV (12 bytes)] [AES-256-GCM ciphertext + auth tag]`. The 3-byte prefix `0x535745` marks encrypted payloads; older unencrypted data is detected by its absence, which keeps the reader backward compatible.\n\nBecause the key is deterministic from the wallet signature, recovery on a new device only needs the wallet \u2014 no cloud key store.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:48.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:48.000Z"
    }
  },
